ATCHISON, T. & S. F. RY. CO. v. SWEARINGEN. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. December 11, 1916.) No. 2948. In Error to the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Texas; William B. Sheppard, Judge. J. W. Terry and A. H. Culwell, both of Galveston, Tex., for plaintiff in error. S. Engelking, of San Antonio, Tex., for defendant in error.

Before PARDEE and WALKER, Circuit Judges, and FOSTER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

We find none of the assignments of error well taken. The judgment of the District Court is affirmed.
